    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two horizontal parallel lines. A vertical arrow pointing downward to the middle of the lines is labeled Incident Infrared Waves. The medium above the top line is Air. The medium between the two lines is Thin Coating, where n is greater than 1.45. The medium below the bottom line is Glass, where n equals 1.45.\" src=\"/images/89b2dd555d1bf75dc392dfa7532b6901.svg\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Infrared waves of wavelength <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"900 nanometers\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"900 nanometers\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>900</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>nm</mi></math></span></span> in air are incident normally on a thin layer of material that coats a glass object, as shown in the figure. The thickness of the coating is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"150 nanometers\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"150 nanometers\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>150</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi>nm</mi></math></span></span>. The refractive index of the glass is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.45\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1.45\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.45</mn></math></span></span>, and the refractive index of the coating is greater than the refractive index of the glass. If the light reflecting off the air-coating and coating-glass interfaces completely interferes destructively in the air, which of the following could be the refractive index of the coating?</p>\n",
